---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy">
  <div class="container py-16 max-w-4xl">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-heading font-bold mb-8">Privacy Policy</h1>
    
    <div class="prose prose-slate max-w-none">
      <p class="text-slate-600 mb-6">Last updated: December 24, 2025</p>
      
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">1. Data Controller</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        The data controller for this website is:<br>
        Rufus Plaga<br>
        Email: <a href="mailto:plagarufus@gmail.com" class="text-red-600 hover:text-red-700">plagarufus@gmail.com</a>
      </p>
      
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">2. General Information</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        This website does not actively collect or store personal data on its own servers. However, the following third-party services used to provide this website may collect and process data as described below.
      </p>
      
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">3. Third-Party Services and Data Processing</h2>
      
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">3.1 GitHub Pages (Hosting Provider)</h3>
      <p class="mb-4">
        This website is hosted on GitHub Pages, a service provided by GitHub Inc., 88 Colin P Kelly Jr St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-4">
        <strong>Data automatically collected by GitHub:</strong>
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4">
        <li>IP address</li>
        <li>Date and time of access</li>
        <li>Pages visited</li>
        <li>Browser type and version</li>
        <li>Operating system</li>
        <li>Referrer URL (previously visited page)</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mb-4">
        <strong>Purpose:</strong> Technical provision, security, and operation of the website.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-4">
        <strong>Legal basis:</strong> Art. 6 para. 1 lit. f GDPR (legitimate interest in technical provision and security of the website).
      </p>
      <p class="mb-4">
        <strong>Retention period:</strong> GitHub stores this data for a maximum of 90 days.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-4">
        More information: <a href="https://docs.github.com/en/site-policy/privacy-policies/github-privacy-statement" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-red-600 hover:text-red-700">GitHub Privacy Statement</a>
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">3.2 GoDaddy (DNS Provider)</h3>
      <p class="mb-4">
        The domain for this website is managed by GoDaddy.com LLC, 14455 N. Hayden Road, Suite 219, Scottsdale, AZ 85260, USA.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-4">
        <strong>Data processed by GoDaddy:</strong> During DNS queries (when your browser resolves the domain name), GoDaddy may process technical data such as IP addresses.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-4">
        <strong>Purpose:</strong> DNS resolution and domain management.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-4">
        <strong>Legal basis:</strong> Art. 6 para. 1 lit. f GDPR (legitimate interest in technical provision of the website).
      </p>
      <p class="mb-4">
        More information: <a href="https://www.godaddy.com/legal/agreements/privacy-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-red-600 hover:text-red-700">GoDaddy Privacy Policy</a>
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">3.3 Google Analytics (Optional - Requires Consent)</h3>
      <p class="mb-4">
        This website uses Google Analytics, a web analytics service provided by Google Ireland Limited, Gordon House, Barrow Street, Dublin 4, Ireland ("Google").
      </p>
      <p class="mb-4">
        <strong>Important:</strong> Google Analytics is only activated if you explicitly accept cookies via the cookie consent banner. Without your consent, no tracking data is collected by Google Analytics.
      </p>
      
      <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-4 mb-2">Data collected by Google Analytics (with consent):</h4>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4">
        <li>Pages visited and time spent on site</li>
        <li>Browser type and version</li>
        <li>Operating system and device type</li>
        <li>Approximate geographic location (country/city level)</li>
        <li>Referral source</li>
        <li>IP address (anonymized)</li>
      </ul>
      
      <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-4 mb-2">IP Anonymization:</h4>
      <p class="mb-4">
        IP anonymization ("anonymizeIP") is activated. Your IP address is shortened by Google within EU member states before being transmitted to the USA. Only in exceptional cases will the full IP address be transmitted to a Google server in the USA and shortened there.
      </p>
      
      <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-4 mb-2">Purpose:</h4>
      <p class="mb-4">
        Analysis of website usage to improve user experience.
      </p>
      
      <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-4 mb-2">Legal basis:</h4>
      <p class="mb-4">
        Art. 6 para. 1 lit. a GDPR (your explicit consent via the cookie banner).
      </p>
      
      <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-4 mb-2">Data transfer:</h4>
      <p class="mb-4">
        Data transfer to the USA is based on the EU-U.S. Data Privacy Framework.
      </p>
      
      <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-4 mb-2">Retention period:</h4>
      <p class="mb-4">
        Google stores the data collected by cookies for 14 months.
      </p>
      
      <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-4 mb-2">Withdraw consent:</h4>
      <p class="mb-4">
        You can withdraw your consent at any time by:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4">
        <li>Deleting your browser cookies</li>
        <li>Declining the cookie banner when it appears again</li>
        <li>Installing the <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-red-600 hover:text-red-700">Google Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on</a></li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mb-4">
        More information: <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-red-600 hover:text-red-700">Google Privacy Policy</a>
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">4. Cookies</h2>
      
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">4.1 Technically Necessary Cookie (No Consent Required)</h3>
      <p class="mb-4">
        <strong>Consent Cookie:</strong> This website stores one cookie to remember your cookie consent choice.
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4">
        <li><strong>Name:</strong> cookieConsent</li>
        <li><strong>Purpose:</strong> Remember whether you accepted or declined cookies</li>
        <li><strong>Content:</strong> Only "accepted" or "declined" - no personal data</li>
        <li><strong>Retention:</strong> 365 days</li>
        <li><strong>Legal basis:</strong> Art. 6 para. 1 lit. f GDPR (necessary for consent management)</li>
      </ul>
      
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">4.2 Optional Analytics Cookies (Requires Consent)</h3>
      <p class="mb-4">
        Google Analytics cookies are only set if you accept them via the cookie banner. See Section 3.3 for details.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">5. Contact via Email</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        If you contact us via email at <a href="mailto:plagarufus@gmail.com" class="text-red-600 hover:text-red-700">plagarufus@gmail.com</a>, your email content (email address, name, message) will only be used to respond to your inquiry.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-4">
        <strong>Purpose:</strong> Responding to your inquiry.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-4">
        <strong>Legal basis:</strong> Art. 6 para. 1 lit. b GDPR (pre-contractual measures) or Art. 6 para. 1 lit. f GDPR (legitimate interest in responding).
      </p>
      <p class="mb-4">
        <strong>Retention:</strong> Your email will be deleted after your inquiry has been fully processed, unless legal retention obligations apply.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-4">
        <strong>Note:</strong> Email communication may be stored on email servers (e.g., Gmail). Please refer to your email provider's privacy policy for details on their data processing.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">6. External Links</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        This website may contain links to external third-party websites (e.g., GitHub, LinkedIn). We have no control over the content or privacy practices of these websites and assume no responsibility for them. Please review the privacy policies of those websites.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">7. Your Rights Under GDPR</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        You have the following rights regarding your personal data:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4">
        <li><strong>Right of access (Art. 15 GDPR):</strong> Request information about your data processed by the third-party services mentioned above.</li>
        <li><strong>Right to rectification (Art. 16 GDPR):</strong> Request correction of inaccurate data.</li>
        <li><strong>Right to erasure (Art. 17 GDPR):</strong> Request deletion of your data.</li>
        <li><strong>Right to restriction (Art. 18 GDPR):</strong> Request restriction of data processing.</li>
        <li><strong>Right to data portability (Art. 20 GDPR):</strong> Receive your data in a structured, machine-readable format.</li>
        <li><strong>Right to object (Art. 21 GDPR):</strong> Object to data processing.</li>
        <li><strong>Right to withdraw consent (Art. 7 para. 3 GDPR):</strong> Withdraw your consent for Google Analytics at any time.</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mb-4">
        <strong>Important:</strong> Since data is primarily collected by third-party services (GitHub, GoDaddy, Google), you may need to contact these providers directly to exercise your rights. For Google Analytics, you can withdraw consent via the methods described in Section 3.3.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-4">
        For questions or to exercise your rights, contact: 
        <a href="mailto:plagarufus@gmail.com" class="text-red-600 hover:text-red-700">plagarufus@gmail.com</a>
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">8. Right to Lodge a Complaint</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        You have the right to lodge a complaint with a data protection supervisory authority if you believe your data is being processed unlawfully. The competent authority is typically the data protection authority of your country of residence.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">9. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        This privacy policy may be updated to reflect changes in services or legal requirements. The current version and date will always be displayed on this page.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>